<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Teltron lifts yr share, div up.</title>
<headline>Teltron lifts yr share, div up.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-06-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended April 30</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>Shr, (cts)</p>
<p>    - headline		42.8	  vs 39.0</p>
<p>    - attrib		  40.3	  vs 43.1</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		 14.2	  vs nil</p>
<p>    Attrib income	   22.47	 vs 24.00</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		   32.39	 vs 36.89</p>
<p>    Tax			  9.98	 vs 12.88</p>
<p>    Interest paid	    6.41	 vs  3.06</p>
<p>    Turnover		 445.43	 vs 373.57</p>
<p>    Exceptional items	4.09 loss  vs  3.50 gain</p>
<p>Full name: Teltron Ltd (Industrial - stores)</p>
<p>NOTE - The company said it would award capitalisation shares to shareholders registered on July 18. It said the number of capitalisation shares to which shareholders would become entitled would be determined by the ratio that 14.2 cents multiplied by 1.06 bears to the weighted average price of the company's shares on the Johannesburg Stock Exchange for three business days ending August 14.</p>
<p>The company added that while the economic climate continued to be a difficult and challenging one, strategies defined by the new management had identified further cost saving opportunities and prospective prospects for the enhancement of the core photographic business.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
